iff_url": "https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/pull/5749.diff", "patch_url": "https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/pull/5749.patch"}, "body_html": "<p>This now works:</p>\n<pre><code>Tensor x = ...;\nScalar i(5);\nx[i]\n</code></pre>\n<p>and more importantly</p>\n<pre><code>Tensor x = ...;\nTensor i = CPU(kInt).ones({});\nx[i]\n</code></pre>\n<p>Since integral literals convert implicitly to <code>Scalar</code>, the old behavior of <code>x[5]</code> is preserved.</p>\n<p>Proper error checking should be taken care of.</p>\n<p><span class=\"issue-keyword tooltipped tooltipped-se\" aria-label=\"This pull request closes issue #3971.\">Fixes</span> <a class=\"issue-link js-issue-link\" data-error-text=\"Failed to load issue title\" data-id=\"278570356\" data-permission-text=\"Issue title is private\" data-url=\"https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/issues/3971\" data-hovercard-type=\"issue\" data-hovercard-url=\"/pytorch/pytorch/issues/3971/hovercard\" href=\"https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/issues/3971\">#3971</a><br>\nPart of <a class=\"issue-link js-issue-link\" data-error-text=\"Failed to load issue title\" data-id=\"287961179\" data-permission-text=\"Issue title is private\" data-url=\"https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/issues/4619\" data-hovercard-type=\"issue\" data-hovercard-url=\"/pytorch/pytorch/issues/4619/hovercard\" href=\"https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/issues/4619\">#4619</a></p>\n<p><a class=\"user-mention\" data-hovercard-type=\"user\" data-hovercard-url=\"/hovercards?user_id=655866\" data-octo-click=\"hovercard-link-click\" data-octo-dimensions=\"link_type:self\" href=\"https://github.com/colesbury\">@colesbury</a> <a class=\"user-mention\" data-hovercard-type=\"user\" data-hovercard-url=\"/hovercards?user_id=370202\" data-octo-click=\"hovercard-link-click\" data-octo-dimensions=\"link_type:self\" href=\"https://github.com/zdevito\">@zdevito</a> <a class=\"user-mention\" data-hovercard-type=\"user\" data-hovercard-url=\"/hovercards?user_id=4583066\" data-octo-click=\"hovercard-link-click\" data-octo-dimensions=\"link_type:self\" href=\"https://github.com/apaszke\">@apaszke</a> <a class=\"user-mention\" data-hovercard-type=\"user\" data-hovercard-url=\"/hovercards?user_id=13564\" data-octo-click=\"hovercard-link-click\" data-octo-dimensions=\"link_type:self\" href=\"https://github.com/ezyang\">@ezyang</a></p>\n<p>CC <a class=\"user-mention\" data-hovercard-type=\"user\" data-hovercard-url=\"/hovercards?user_id=3605224\" data-octo-click=\"hovercard-link-click\" data-octo-dimensions=\"link_type:self\" href=\"https://github.com/ebetica\">@ebetica</a></p>", "body_text": "This now works:\nTensor x = ...;\nScalar i(5);\nx[i]\n\nand more importantly\nTensor x = ...;\nTensor i = CPU(kInt).ones({});\nx[i]\n\nSince integral literals convert implicitly to Scalar, the old behavior of x[5] is preserved.\nProper error checking should be taken care of.\nFixes #3971\nPart of #4619\n@colesbury @zdevito @apaszke @ezyang\nCC @ebetica", "body": "This now works:\r\n\r\n```\r\nTensor x = ...;\r\nScalar i(5);\r\nx[i]\r\n```\r\n\r\nand more importantly\r\n\r\n```\r\nTensor x = ...;\r\nTensor i = CPU(kInt).ones({});\r\nx[i]\r\n```\r\n\r\nSince integral literals convert implicitly to `Scalar`, the old behavior of `x[5]` is preserved.\r\n\r\nProper error checking should be taken care of.\r\n\r\nFixes https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/issues/3971\r\nPart of https://github.com/pytorch/pytorch/issues/4619\r\n\r\n@colesbury @zdevito @apaszke @ezyang \r\n\r\nCC @ebetica "}